(this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]=this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]||[]).push([[9],{162:function(e,n,a){"use strict";a.r(n);var t=a(1),i=a(54),s=(a(0),a(8)),o=a(82),r=a.n(o),h=a(21),c="\n# Background\n\nInitially I was born in Missouri and moved around different states growing up such as Alabama, Virgina, and Florida. Finally my family and I ended up in Olathe, Kansas around 2008. In high school I played tennis, soccer, and one year of bowling!\n\n# Education\n\nIn high school, programming was not on my radar. In fact, I was struggling to pass pre-calc! After graduating I attended Southwest Baptist as an accounting major for one year. I wanted to be an engineer but was afraid of failing all the hideous math that was required. Flash forward three years and I am graduating with a degree in computer science. Remember how I was said I was scared of math? I took that fear and used it as motivation to study as hard as I could and the fruits that brought was\nbeing invtied to take honors math courses in the mathematics department! It goes to show that you cant let fear hold you back, sometimes you need to take a leap of faith!\n\n# Research\n\nThe biggest passion I have recently stumbled upon has been the research I have been conducting at the University of Kansas alongside the Dean of Engineering, Arvin Agah.\nWe have been researching how machine learning, more specifically neural networks, can enhance the quality of speech and block out unwanted noise in hearing aids. Hearing aids have a problem in that it does not enhance specific noise, but all noise. To accomplish this, we have been applying many machine learning algorithms such as convolutional neural networks and auto-encoders. Currently, we are working on a paper that uses a new domain of machine learning called self-supervised learning.\n<br>\n<br>\n\nResearch has been the most awarding activity I have done in college. It is so thrilling to work on a problem that no one has proposed a solution to yet. This has shown me that research is something I want to be a part of for the rest of my life.\n\n# Internships\n\nLast summer I had my first software engineering internship at Kiewit! Kiewit is one of the largest construction companies in the nation and it was exciting to learn\nhow software was created in handled in the industry. Over the couse of the summer I used numerous technologies such as Angular, .NET, .NET Core, and SQL! I got to build full stack applications that helped the efficiency of many projects happening at Kiewit. The biggest takeaway from the summer was not the technologies I learned, but how to learn the technologies. As the field of computer science grows and grows you will need to be up to date with everything that is happening. That is why knowing how\nto understand new technologies is so important!\n",l=c.split(/\s+/).map((function(e){return e.replace(/\W/g,"")})).filter((function(e){return e.length})).length,d=function(e){var n=Object.assign({},e);return Object(t.jsx)(s.b,Object(i.a)({},n))};n.default=function(){return Object(t.jsx)(h.a,{title:"About",description:"Learn about Michael D'Angelo",children:Object(t.jsxs)("article",{className:"post markdown",id:"about",children:[Object(t.jsx)("header",{children:Object(t.jsxs)("div",{className:"title",children:[Object(t.jsx)("h2",{"data-testid":"heading",children:Object(t.jsx)(s.b,{to:"/about",children:"About Me"})}),Object(t.jsxs)("p",{children:["(in about ",l," words)"]})]})}),Object(t.jsx)(r.a,{source:c,renderers:{Link:d},escapeHtml:!1})]})})}}}]);
